112IntRect DragCaretController::caretRectInRootViewCoordinates() const
113{
114 if (!hasCaret())
115 return { };
116
117 if (auto* document = m_position.deepEquivalent().document()) {
118 if (auto* documentView = document->view())
119 return documentView->contentsToRootView(m_position.absoluteCaretBounds());
120 }
121
122 return { };
123}
124
125IntRect DragCaretController::editableElementRectInRootViewCoordinates() const
126{
127 if (!hasCaret())
128 return { };
129
130 RefPtr<ContainerNode> editableContainer;
131 if (auto* formControl = enclosingTextFormControl(m_position.deepEquivalent()))
132 editableContainer = formControl;
133 else
134 editableContainer = highestEditableRoot(m_position.deepEquivalent());
135
136 if (!editableContainer)
137 return { };
138
139 auto* renderer = editableContainer->renderer();
140 if (!renderer)
141 return { };
142
143 if (auto* view = editableContainer->document().view())
144 return view->contentsToRootView(renderer->absoluteBoundingBoxRect()); // FIXME: Wrong for elements with visible layout overflow.
145
146 return { };
147}

149static inline bool shouldAlwaysUseDirectionalSelection(Document* document)
150{
151 return !document || document->editor().behavior().shouldConsiderSelectionAsDirectional();
152}

154FrameSelection::FrameSelection(Document* document)
155 : m_document(makeWeakPtr(document))
156 , m_granularity(TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity)
157#if ENABLE(TEXT_CARET)
158 , m_caretBlinkTimer(*this, &FrameSelection::caretBlinkTimerFired)
159#endif
160 , m_appearanceUpdateTimer(*this, &FrameSelection::appearanceUpdateTimerFired)
161 , m_caretInsidePositionFixed(false)
162 , m_absCaretBoundsDirty(true)
163 , m_caretPaint(true)
164 , m_isCaretBlinkingSuspended(false)
165 , m_focused(document && document->frame() && document->page() && document->page()->focusController().focusedFrame() == document->frame())
166 , m_shouldShowBlockCursor(false)
167 , m_pendingSelectionUpdate(false)
168 , m_alwaysAlignCursorOnScrollWhenRevealingSelection(false)
169#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
170 , m_updateAppearanceEnabled(false)
171 , m_caretBlinks(true)
172#endif
173{
174 if (shouldAlwaysUseDirectionalSelection(m_document.get()))
175 m_selection.setIsDirectional(true);
176
177 bool activeAndFocused = isFocusedAndActive();
178 if (activeAndFocused)
179 setSelectionFromNone();
180#if USE(UIKIT_EDITING)
181 // Caret blinking (blinks | does not blink)
182 setCaretVisible(activeAndFocused);
183#else
184 setCaretVisibility(activeAndFocused ? Visible : Hidden, ShouldUpdateAppearance::No);
185#endif
186}

217void FrameSelection::moveWithoutValidationTo(const Position& base, const Position& extent, bool selectionHasDirection, bool shouldSetFocus, SelectionRevealMode revealMode, const AXTextStateChangeIntent& intent)
218{
219 VisibleSelection newSelection;
220 newSelection.setWithoutValidation(base, extent);
221 newSelection.setIsDirectional(selectionHasDirection);
222 AXTextStateChangeIntent newIntent = intent.type == AXTextStateChangeTypeUnknown ? AXTextStateChangeIntent(AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionMove, AXTextSelection { AXTextSelectionDirectionDiscontiguous, AXTextSelectionGranularityUnknown, false }) : intent;
223 auto options = defaultSetSelectionOptions();
224 if (!shouldSetFocus)
225 options.add(DoNotSetFocus);
226 switch (revealMode) {
227 case SelectionRevealMode::DoNotReveal:
228 break;
229 case SelectionRevealMode::Reveal:
230 options.add(RevealSelection);
231 break;
232 case SelectionRevealMode::RevealUpToMainFrame:
233 options.add(RevealSelectionUpToMainFrame);
234 break;
235 }
236 setSelection(newSelection, options, newIntent);
237}

239void DragCaretController::setCaretPosition(const VisiblePosition& position)
240{
241 if (Node* node = m_position.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode())
242 invalidateCaretRect(node);
243 m_position = position;
244 setCaretRectNeedsUpdate();
245 Document* document = nullptr;
246 if (Node* node = m_position.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()) {
247 invalidateCaretRect(node);
248 document = &node->document();
249 }
250 if (m_position.isNull() || m_position.isOrphan())
251 clearCaretRect();
252 else
253 updateCaretRect(*document, m_position);
254}

256static void adjustEndpointsAtBidiBoundary(VisiblePosition& visibleBase, VisiblePosition& visibleExtent)
257{
258 RenderedPosition base(visibleBase);
259 RenderedPosition extent(visibleExtent);
260
261 if (base.isNull() || extent.isNull() || base.isEquivalent(extent))
262 return;
263
264 if (base.atLeftBoundaryOfBidiRun()) {
265 if (!extent.atRightBoundaryOfBidiRun(base.bidiLevelOnRight())
266 && base.isEquivalent(extent.leftBoundaryOfBidiRun(base.bidiLevelOnRight()))) {
267 visibleBase = base.positionAtLeftBoundaryOfBiDiRun();
268 return;
269 }
270 return;
271 }
272
273 if (base.atRightBoundaryOfBidiRun()) {
274 if (!extent.atLeftBoundaryOfBidiRun(base.bidiLevelOnLeft())
275 && base.isEquivalent(extent.rightBoundaryOfBidiRun(base.bidiLevelOnLeft()))) {
276 visibleBase = base.positionAtRightBoundaryOfBiDiRun();
277 return;
278 }
279 return;
280 }
281
282 if (extent.atLeftBoundaryOfBidiRun() && extent.isEquivalent(base.leftBoundaryOfBidiRun(extent.bidiLevelOnRight()))) {
283 visibleExtent = extent.positionAtLeftBoundaryOfBiDiRun();
284 return;
285 }
286
287 if (extent.atRightBoundaryOfBidiRun() && extent.isEquivalent(base.rightBoundaryOfBidiRun(extent.bidiLevelOnLeft()))) {
288 visibleExtent = extent.positionAtRightBoundaryOfBiDiRun();
289 return;
290 }
291}

293void FrameSelection::setSelectionByMouseIfDifferent(const VisibleSelection& passedNewSelection, TextGranularity granularity,
294 EndPointsAdjustmentMode endpointsAdjustmentMode)
295{
296 VisibleSelection newSelection = passedNewSelection;
297 bool isDirectional = shouldAlwaysUseDirectionalSelection(m_document.get()) || newSelection.isDirectional();
298
299 VisiblePosition base = m_originalBase.isNotNull() ? m_originalBase : newSelection.visibleBase();
300 VisiblePosition newBase = base;
301 VisiblePosition extent = newSelection.visibleExtent();
302 VisiblePosition newExtent = extent;
303 if (endpointsAdjustmentMode == EndPointsAdjustmentMode::AdjustAtBidiBoundary)
304 adjustEndpointsAtBidiBoundary(newBase, newExtent);
305
306 if (newBase != base || newExtent != extent) {
307 m_originalBase = base;
308 newSelection.setBase(newBase);
309 newSelection.setExtent(newExtent);
310 } else if (m_originalBase.isNotNull()) {
311 if (m_selection.base() == newSelection.base())
312 newSelection.setBase(m_originalBase);
313 m_originalBase = { };
314 }
315
316 newSelection.setIsDirectional(isDirectional); // Adjusting base and extent will make newSelection always directional
317 if (m_selection == newSelection || !shouldChangeSelection(newSelection))
318 return;
319
320 AXTextStateChangeIntent intent;
321 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled() && newSelection.isCaret())
322 intent = AXTextStateChangeIntent(AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionMove, AXTextSelection { AXTextSelectionDirectionDiscontiguous, AXTextSelectionGranularityUnknown, false });
323 else
324 intent = AXTextStateChangeIntent();
325 setSelection(newSelection, defaultSetSelectionOptions() | FireSelectEvent, intent, AlignCursorOnScrollIfNeeded, granularity);
326}

328bool FrameSelection::setSelectionWithoutUpdatingAppearance(const VisibleSelection& newSelectionPossiblyWithoutDirection, OptionSet<SetSelectionOption> options, CursorAlignOnScroll align, TextGranularity granularity)
329{
330 bool closeTyping = options.contains(CloseTyping);
331 bool shouldClearTypingStyle = options.contains(ClearTypingStyle);
332
333 VisibleSelection newSelection = newSelectionPossiblyWithoutDirection;
334 if (shouldAlwaysUseDirectionalSelection(m_document.get()))
335 newSelection.setIsDirectional(true);
336
337 // <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=23464>: Infinite recursion at FrameSelection::setSelection
338 // if document->frame() == m_document->frame() we can get into an infinite loop
339 if (Document* newSelectionDocument = newSelection.base().document()) {
340 if (RefPtr<Frame> newSelectionFrame = newSelectionDocument->frame()) {
341 if (m_document && newSelectionFrame != m_document->frame() && newSelectionDocument != m_document) {
342 newSelectionDocument->selection().setSelection(newSelection, options, AXTextStateChangeIntent(), align, granularity);
343 // It's possible that during the above set selection, this FrameSelection has been modified by
344 // selectFrameElementInParentIfFullySelected, but that the selection is no longer valid since
345 // the frame is about to be destroyed. If this is the case, clear our selection.
346 if (newSelectionFrame->hasOneRef() && m_selection.isNoneOrOrphaned())
347 clear();
348 return false;
349 }
350 }
351 }
352
353 VisibleSelection oldSelection = m_selection;
354 bool willMutateSelection = oldSelection != newSelection;
355 if (willMutateSelection && m_document)
356 m_document->editor().selectionWillChange();
357
358 {
359 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
360 if (newSelection.isOrphan()) {
361 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
362 clear();
363 return false;
364 }
365
366 if (!m_document || (!m_document->frame() && !newSelection.document())) {
367 m_selection = newSelection;
368 updateAssociatedLiveRange();
369 return false;
370 }
371
372 bool selectionEndpointsBelongToMultipleDocuments = newSelection.base().document() && !newSelection.document();
373 bool selectionIsInAnotherDocument = newSelection.document() && newSelection.document() != m_document.get();
374 bool selectionIsInDetachedDocument = newSelection.document() && !newSelection.document()->frame();
375 if (selectionEndpointsBelongToMultipleDocuments || selectionIsInAnotherDocument || selectionIsInDetachedDocument) {
376 clear();
377 return false;
378 }
379 ASSERT(m_document->frame());
380
381 if (closeTyping)
382 TypingCommand::closeTyping(*m_document);
383
384 if (shouldClearTypingStyle)
385 clearTypingStyle();
386
387 m_granularity = granularity;
388 m_selection = newSelection;
389 updateAssociatedLiveRange();
390 }
391
392 // Selection offsets should increase when LF is inserted before the caret in InsertLineBreakCommand. See <https://webkit.org/b/56061>.
393 if (HTMLTextFormControlElement* textControl = enclosingTextFormControl(newSelection.start()))
394 textControl->selectionChanged(options.contains(FireSelectEvent));
395
396 if (!willMutateSelection)
397 return false;
398
399 setCaretRectNeedsUpdate();
400
401 if (!newSelection.isNone() && !(options & DoNotSetFocus)) {
402 auto* oldFocusedElement = m_document->focusedElement();
403 setFocusedElementIfNeeded();
404 if (!m_document->frame())
405 return false;
406 // FIXME: Should not be needed.
407 if (m_document->focusedElement() != oldFocusedElement)
408 m_document->updateStyleIfNeeded();
409 }
410
411 // Always clear the x position used for vertical arrow navigation.
412 // It will be restored by the vertical arrow navigation code if necessary.
413 m_xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation = std::nullopt;
414 selectFrameElementInParentIfFullySelected();
415 m_document->editor().respondToChangedSelection(oldSelection, options);
416 // https://www.w3.org/TR/selection-api/#selectionchange-event
417 // FIXME: Spec doesn't specify which task source to use.
418 m_document->queueTaskToDispatchEvent(TaskSource::UserInteraction, Event::create(eventNames().selectionchangeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
419
420 return true;
421}

423void FrameSelection::setSelection(const VisibleSelection& selection, OptionSet<SetSelectionOption> options, AXTextStateChangeIntent intent, CursorAlignOnScroll align, TextGranularity granularity)
424{
425 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Selection, stream << "FrameSelection::setSelection " << selection);
426
427 auto protectedDocument = makeRefPtr(m_document.get());
428 if (!setSelectionWithoutUpdatingAppearance(selection, options, align, granularity))
429 return;
430
431 if (options & RevealSelectionUpToMainFrame)
432 m_selectionRevealMode = SelectionRevealMode::RevealUpToMainFrame;
433 else if (options & RevealSelection)
434 m_selectionRevealMode = SelectionRevealMode::Reveal;
435 else
436 m_selectionRevealMode = SelectionRevealMode::DoNotReveal;
437 m_alwaysAlignCursorOnScrollWhenRevealingSelection = align == AlignCursorOnScrollAlways;
438
439 m_selectionRevealIntent = intent;
440 m_pendingSelectionUpdate = true;
441
442 if (protectedDocument->hasPendingStyleRecalc())
443 return;
444
445 auto frameView = protectedDocument->view();
446 if (frameView && frameView->layoutContext().isLayoutPending())
447 return;
448
449 updateAndRevealSelection(intent, options.contains(SmoothScroll) ? ScrollBehavior::Smooth : ScrollBehavior::Instant, options.contains(OverrideSmoothScrollFeatureEnablement) ? SmoothScrollFeatureEnablement::Override : SmoothScrollFeatureEnablement::Default);
450
451 if (options & IsUserTriggered) {
452 if (auto* client = protectedDocument->editor().client())
453 client->didEndUserTriggeredSelectionChanges();
454 }
455}
456
457static void updateSelectionByUpdatingLayoutOrStyle(Document& document)
458{
459#if ENABLE(TEXT_CARET)
460 document.updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
461#else
462 document.updateStyleIfNeeded();
463#endif
464}

466void FrameSelection::setNeedsSelectionUpdate(RevealSelectionAfterUpdate revealMode)
467{
468 m_selectionRevealIntent = AXTextStateChangeIntent();
469 if (revealMode == RevealSelectionAfterUpdate::Forced)
470 m_selectionRevealMode = SelectionRevealMode::Reveal;
471 m_pendingSelectionUpdate = true;
472 if (RenderView* view = m_document->renderView())
473 view->selection().clear();
474}
475
476void FrameSelection::updateAndRevealSelection(const AXTextStateChangeIntent& intent, ScrollBehavior scrollBehavior, SmoothScrollFeatureEnablement overideFeatureEnablement)
477{
478 if (!m_pendingSelectionUpdate)
479 return;
480
481 m_pendingSelectionUpdate = false;
482
483 updateAppearance();
484
485 if (m_selectionRevealMode != SelectionRevealMode::DoNotReveal) {
486 ScrollAlignment alignment;
487
488 if (m_document->editor().behavior().shouldCenterAlignWhenSelectionIsRevealed())
489 alignment = m_alwaysAlignCursorOnScrollWhenRevealingSelection ? ScrollAlignment::alignCenterAlways : ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded;
490 else
491 alignment = m_alwaysAlignCursorOnScrollWhenRevealingSelection ? ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways : ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded;
492
493 revealSelection(m_selectionRevealMode, alignment, RevealExtent, scrollBehavior, overideFeatureEnablement);
494 }
495
496 notifyAccessibilityForSelectionChange(intent);
497}

506static bool removingNodeRemovesPosition(Node& node, const Position& position)
507{
508 if (!position.anchorNode())
509 return false;
510
511 if (position.anchorNode() == &node)
512 return true;
513
514 if (!is<Element>(node))
515 return false;
516
517 return downcast<Element>(node).containsIncludingShadowDOM(position.anchorNode());
518}
519
520void DragCaretController::nodeWillBeRemoved(Node& node)
521{
522 if (!hasCaret() || !node.isConnected())
523 return;
524
525 if (!removingNodeRemovesPosition(node, m_position.deepEquivalent()))
526 return;
527
528 if (RenderView* view = node.document().renderView())
529 view->selection().clear();
530
531 clear();
532}
533
534void FrameSelection::nodeWillBeRemoved(Node& node)
535{
536 // There can't be a selection inside a fragment, so if a fragment's node is being removed,
537 // the selection in the document that created the fragment needs no adjustment.
538 if (isNone() || !node.isConnected())
539 return;
540
541 respondToNodeModification(node, removingNodeRemovesPosition(node, m_selection.base()), removingNodeRemovesPosition(node, m_selection.extent()),
542 removingNodeRemovesPosition(node, m_selection.start()), removingNodeRemovesPosition(node, m_selection.end()));
543}
544
545void FrameSelection::respondToNodeModification(Node& node, bool baseRemoved, bool extentRemoved, bool startRemoved, bool endRemoved)
546{
547 bool clearRenderTreeSelection = false;
548 bool clearDOMTreeSelection = false;
549
550 if (startRemoved || endRemoved) {
551 Position start = m_selection.start();
552 Position end = m_selection.end();
553 if (startRemoved)
554 updatePositionForNodeRemoval(start, node);
555 if (endRemoved)
556 updatePositionForNodeRemoval(end, node);
557
558 if (start.isNotNull() && end.isNotNull()) {
559 if (m_selection.isBaseFirst())
560 m_selection.setWithoutValidation(start, end);
561 else
562 m_selection.setWithoutValidation(end, start);
563 } else
564 clearDOMTreeSelection = true;
565
566 clearRenderTreeSelection = true;
567 } else if (baseRemoved || extentRemoved) {
568 // The base and/or extent are about to be removed, but the start and end aren't.
569 // Change the base and extent to the start and end, but don't re-validate the
570 // selection, since doing so could move the start and end into the node
571 // that is about to be removed.
572 if (m_selection.isBaseFirst())
573 m_selection.setWithoutValidation(m_selection.start(), m_selection.end());
574 else
575 m_selection.setWithoutValidation(m_selection.end(), m_selection.start());
576 } else if (isRange()) {
577 if (auto range = m_selection.firstRange(); range && intersects<ComposedTree>(*range, node)) {
578 // If we did nothing here, when this node's renderer was destroyed, the rect that it
579 // occupied would be invalidated, but, selection gaps that change as a result of
580 // the removal wouldn't be invalidated.
581 // FIXME: Don't do so much unnecessary invalidation.
582 clearRenderTreeSelection = true;
583 }
584 }
585
586 if (clearRenderTreeSelection) {
587 if (auto* renderView = node.document().renderView()) {
588 renderView->selection().clear();
589
590 // Trigger a selection update so the selection will be set again.
591 m_selectionRevealIntent = AXTextStateChangeIntent();
592 m_pendingSelectionUpdate = true;
593 renderView->frameView().scheduleSelectionUpdate();
594 }
595 }
596
597 if (clearDOMTreeSelection)
598 setSelection(VisibleSelection(), DoNotSetFocus);
599}
600
601static void updatePositionAfterAdoptingTextReplacement(Position& position, CharacterData* node, unsigned offset, unsigned oldLength, unsigned newLength)
602{
603 if (!position.anchorNode() || position.anchorNode() != node || position.anchorType() != Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor)
604 return;
605
606 // See: http://www.w3.org/TR/DOM-Level-2-Traversal-Range/ranges.html#Level-2-Range-Mutation
607 ASSERT(position.offsetInContainerNode() >= 0);
608 unsigned positionOffset = static_cast<unsigned>(position.offsetInContainerNode());
609 // Replacing text can be viewed as a deletion followed by insertion.
610 if (positionOffset >= offset && positionOffset <= offset + oldLength)
611 position.moveToOffset(offset);
612
613 // Adjust the offset if the position is after the end of the deleted contents
614 // (positionOffset > offset + oldLength) to avoid having a stale offset.
615 if (positionOffset > offset + oldLength)
616 position.moveToOffset(positionOffset - oldLength + newLength);
617
618 ASSERT(static_cast<unsigned>(position.offsetInContainerNode()) <= node->length());
619}
620
621void FrameSelection::textWasReplaced(CharacterData* node, unsigned offset, unsigned oldLength, unsigned newLength)
622{
623 // The fragment check is a performance optimization. See http://trac.webkit.org/changeset/30062.
624 if (isNone() || !node || !node->isConnected())
625 return;
626
627 Position base = m_selection.base();
628 Position extent = m_selection.extent();
629 Position start = m_selection.start();
630 Position end = m_selection.end();
631 updatePositionAfterAdoptingTextReplacement(base, node, offset, oldLength, newLength);
632 updatePositionAfterAdoptingTextReplacement(extent, node, offset, oldLength, newLength);
633 updatePositionAfterAdoptingTextReplacement(start, node, offset, oldLength, newLength);
634 updatePositionAfterAdoptingTextReplacement(end, node, offset, oldLength, newLength);
635
636 if (base != m_selection.base() || extent != m_selection.extent() || start != m_selection.start() || end != m_selection.end()) {
637 VisibleSelection newSelection;
638 if (base != extent)
639 newSelection.setWithoutValidation(base, extent);
640 else if (m_selection.isDirectional() && !m_selection.isBaseFirst())
641 newSelection.setWithoutValidation(end, start);
642 else
643 newSelection.setWithoutValidation(start, end);
644
645 setSelection(newSelection, DoNotSetFocus);
646 }
647}

653
654TextDirection FrameSelection::directionOfSelection()
655{
656 // Get bot VisiblePositions first because visibleStart() and visibleEnd()
657 // can cause layout, which has the potential to invalidate lineboxes.
658 auto startPosition = m_selection.visibleStart();
659 auto endPosition = m_selection.visibleEnd();
660 auto startRun = startPosition.inlineRunAndOffset().run;
661 auto endRun = endPosition.inlineRunAndOffset().run;
662 if (startRun && endRun && startRun->direction() == endRun->direction())
663 return startRun->direction();
664 return directionOfEnclosingBlock();
665}
666
667void FrameSelection::willBeModified(EAlteration alter, SelectionDirection direction)
668{
669 if (alter != AlterationExtend)
670 return;
671
672 Position start = m_selection.start();
673 Position end = m_selection.end();
674
675 bool baseIsStart = true;
676
677 if (m_selection.isDirectional()) {
678 // Make base and extent match start and end so we extend the user-visible selection.
679 // This only matters for cases where base and extend point to different positions than
680 // start and end (e.g. after a double-click to select a word).
681 if (m_selection.isBaseFirst())
682 baseIsStart = true;
683 else
684 baseIsStart = false;
685 } else {
686 switch (direction) {
687 case SelectionDirection::Right:
688 if (directionOfSelection() == TextDirection::LTR)
689 baseIsStart = true;
690 else
691 baseIsStart = false;
692 break;
693 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
694 baseIsStart = true;
695 break;
696 case SelectionDirection::Left:
697 if (directionOfSelection() == TextDirection::LTR)
698 baseIsStart = false;
699 else
700 baseIsStart = true;
701 break;
702 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
703 baseIsStart = false;
704 break;
705 }
706 }
707 if (baseIsStart) {
708 m_selection.setBase(start);
709 m_selection.setExtent(end);
710 } else {
711 m_selection.setBase(end);
712 m_selection.setExtent(start);
713 }
714}
715
716VisiblePosition FrameSelection::positionForPlatform(bool isGetStart) const
717{
718 // FIXME: VisibleSelection should be fixed to ensure as an invariant that
719 // base/extent always point to the same nodes as start/end, but which points
720 // to which depends on the value of isBaseFirst. Then this can be changed
721 // to just return m_sel.extent().
722 if (m_document && m_document->editor().behavior().shouldAlwaysExtendSelectionFromExtentEndpoint())
723 return m_selection.isBaseFirst() ? m_selection.visibleEnd() : m_selection.visibleStart();
724
725 return isGetStart ? m_selection.visibleStart() : m_selection.visibleEnd();
726}
727
728VisiblePosition FrameSelection::startForPlatform() const
729{
730 return positionForPlatform(true);
731}
732
733VisiblePosition FrameSelection::endForPlatform() const
734{
735 return positionForPlatform(false);
736}
737
738VisiblePosition FrameSelection::nextWordPositionForPlatform(const VisiblePosition& originalPosition)
739{
740 VisiblePosition positionAfterCurrentWord = nextWordPosition(originalPosition);
741
742 if (m_document && m_document->editor().behavior().shouldSkipSpaceWhenMovingRight()) {
743 // In order to skip spaces when moving right, we advance one
744 // word further and then move one word back. Given the
745 // semantics of previousWordPosition() this will put us at the
746 // beginning of the word following.
747 VisiblePosition positionAfterSpacingAndFollowingWord = nextWordPosition(positionAfterCurrentWord);
748 if (positionAfterSpacingAndFollowingWord != positionAfterCurrentWord)
749 positionAfterCurrentWord = previousWordPosition(positionAfterSpacingAndFollowingWord);
750
751 bool movingBackwardsMovedPositionToStartOfCurrentWord = positionAfterCurrentWord == previousWordPosition(nextWordPosition(originalPosition));
752 if (movingBackwardsMovedPositionToStartOfCurrentWord)
753 positionAfterCurrentWord = positionAfterSpacingAndFollowingWord;
754 }
755 return positionAfterCurrentWord;
756}
757
758static void adjustPositionForUserSelectAll(VisiblePosition& pos, bool isForward)
759{
760 if (Node* rootUserSelectAll = Position::rootUserSelectAllForNode(pos.deepEquivalent().anchorNode()))
761 pos = isForward ? positionAfterNode(rootUserSelectAll).downstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary) : positionBeforeNode(rootUserSelectAll).upstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary);
762}
763
764VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyExtendingRight(TextGranularity granularity)
765{
766 VisiblePosition pos(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
767
768 // The difference between modifyExtendingRight and modifyExtendingForward is:
769 // modifyExtendingForward always extends forward logically.
770 // modifyExtendingRight behaves the same as modifyExtendingForward except for extending character or word,
771 // it extends forward logically if the enclosing block is TextDirection::LTR,
772 // but it extends backward logically if the enclosing block is TextDirection::RTL.
773 switch (granularity) {
774 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
775 if (directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR)
776 pos = pos.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
777 else
778 pos = pos.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
779 break;
780 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
781 if (directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR)
782 pos = nextWordPositionForPlatform(pos);
783 else
784 pos = previousWordPosition(pos);
785 break;
786 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
787 if (directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR)
788 pos = modifyExtendingForward(granularity);
789 else
790 pos = modifyExtendingBackward(granularity);
791 break;
792 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
793 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
794 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
795 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
796 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
797 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
798 // FIXME: implement all of the above?
799 pos = modifyExtendingForward(granularity);
800 break;
801 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
802 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
803 break;
804 }
805 adjustPositionForUserSelectAll(pos, directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR);
806 return pos;
807}
808
809VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyExtendingForward(TextGranularity granularity)
810{
811 VisiblePosition pos(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
812 switch (granularity) {
813 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
814 pos = pos.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
815 break;
816 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
817 pos = nextWordPositionForPlatform(pos);
818 break;
819 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
820 pos = nextSentencePosition(pos);
821 break;
822 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
823 pos = nextLinePosition(pos, lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Extent));
824 break;
825 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
826 pos = nextParagraphPosition(pos, lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Extent));
827 break;
828 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
829 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
830 break;
831 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
832 pos = endOfSentence(endForPlatform());
833 break;
834 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
835 pos = logicalEndOfLine(endForPlatform());
836 break;
837 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
838 pos = endOfParagraph(endForPlatform());
839 break;
840 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
841 pos = endForPlatform();
842 if (isEditablePosition(pos.deepEquivalent()))
843 pos = endOfEditableContent(pos);
844 else
845 pos = endOfDocument(pos);
846 break;
847 }
848 adjustPositionForUserSelectAll(pos, directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR);
849 return pos;
850}
851
852VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyMovingRight(TextGranularity granularity, bool* reachedBoundary)
853{
854 if (reachedBoundary)
855 *reachedBoundary = false;
856 VisiblePosition pos;
857 switch (granularity) {
858 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
859 if (isRange()) {
860 if (directionOfSelection() == TextDirection::LTR)
861 pos = VisiblePosition(m_selection.end(), m_selection.affinity());
862 else
863 pos = VisiblePosition(m_selection.start(), m_selection.affinity());
864 } else
865 pos = VisiblePosition(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity()).right(true, reachedBoundary);
866 break;
867 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity: {
868 bool skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight = m_document && m_document->editor().behavior().shouldSkipSpaceWhenMovingRight();
869 VisiblePosition currentPosition(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
870 pos = rightWordPosition(currentPosition, skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight);
871 if (reachedBoundary)
872 *reachedBoundary = pos == currentPosition;
873 break;
874 }
875 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
876 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
877 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
878 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
879 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
880 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
881 // FIXME: Implement all of the above.
882 pos = modifyMovingForward(granularity, reachedBoundary);
883 break;
884 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
885 pos = rightBoundaryOfLine(startForPlatform(), directionOfEnclosingBlock(), reachedBoundary);
886 break;
887 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
888 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
889 break;
890 }
891 return pos;
892}
893
894VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyMovingForward(TextGranularity granularity, bool* reachedBoundary)
895{
896 if (reachedBoundary)
897 *reachedBoundary = false;
898 VisiblePosition currentPosition;
899 switch (granularity) {
900 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
901 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
902 currentPosition = VisiblePosition(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
903 break;
904 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
905 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
906 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
907 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
908 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
909 currentPosition = endForPlatform();
910 break;
911 default:
912 break;
913 }
914 VisiblePosition pos;
915 // FIXME: Stay in editable content for the less common granularities.
916 switch (granularity) {
917 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
918 if (isRange())
919 pos = VisiblePosition(m_selection.end(), m_selection.affinity());
920 else
921 pos = VisiblePosition(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity()).next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, reachedBoundary);
922 break;
923 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
924 pos = nextWordPositionForPlatform(currentPosition);
925 break;
926 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
927 pos = nextSentencePosition(currentPosition);
928 break;
929 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity: {
930 // down-arrowing from a range selection that ends at the start of a line needs
931 // to leave the selection at that line start (no need to call nextLinePosition!)
932 pos = currentPosition;
933 if (!isRange() || !isStartOfLine(pos))
934 pos = nextLinePosition(pos, lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Start));
935 break;
936 }
937 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
938 pos = nextParagraphPosition(currentPosition, lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Start));
939 break;
940 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
941 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
942 break;
943 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
944 pos = endOfSentence(currentPosition);
945 break;
946 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
947 pos = logicalEndOfLine(endForPlatform(), reachedBoundary);
948 break;
949 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
950 pos = endOfParagraph(currentPosition);
951 break;
952 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
953 pos = currentPosition;
954 if (isEditablePosition(pos.deepEquivalent()))
955 pos = endOfEditableContent(pos);
956 else
957 pos = endOfDocument(pos);
958 break;
959 }
960 switch (granularity) {
961 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
962 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
963 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
964 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
965 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
966 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
967 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
968 if (reachedBoundary)
969 *reachedBoundary = pos == currentPosition;
970 break;
971 default:
972 break;
973 }
974 return pos;
975}
976
977VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyExtendingLeft(TextGranularity granularity)
978{
979 VisiblePosition pos(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
980
981 // The difference between modifyExtendingLeft and modifyExtendingBackward is:
982 // modifyExtendingBackward always extends backward logically.
983 // modifyExtendingLeft behaves the same as modifyExtendingBackward except for extending character or word,
984 // it extends backward logically if the enclosing block is TextDirection::LTR,
985 // but it extends forward logically if the enclosing block is TextDirection::RTL.
986 switch (granularity) {
987 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
988 if (directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR)
989 pos = pos.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
990 else
991 pos = pos.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
992 break;
993 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
994 if (directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR)
995 pos = previousWordPosition(pos);
996 else
997 pos = nextWordPositionForPlatform(pos);
998 break;
999 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
1000 if (directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR)
1001 pos = modifyExtendingBackward(granularity);
1002 else
1003 pos = modifyExtendingForward(granularity);
1004 break;
1005 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1006 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1007 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1008 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
1009 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
1010 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
1011 pos = modifyExtendingBackward(granularity);
1012 break;
1013 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1014 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1015 break;
1016 }
1017 adjustPositionForUserSelectAll(pos, !(directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR));
1018 return pos;
1019}
1020
1021VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyExtendingBackward(TextGranularity granularity)
1022{
1023 VisiblePosition pos(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
1024
1025 // Extending a selection backward by word or character from just after a table selects
1026 // the table. This "makes sense" from the user perspective, esp. when deleting.
1027 // It was done here instead of in VisiblePosition because we want VPs to iterate
1028 // over everything.
1029 switch (granularity) {
1030 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
1031 pos = pos.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1032 break;
1033 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1034 pos = previousWordPosition(pos);
1035 break;
1036 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1037 pos = previousSentencePosition(pos);
1038 break;
1039 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1040 pos = previousLinePosition(pos, lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Extent));
1041 break;
1042 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1043 pos = previousParagraphPosition(pos, lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Extent));
1044 break;
1045 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
1046 pos = startOfSentence(startForPlatform());
1047 break;
1048 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
1049 pos = logicalStartOfLine(startForPlatform());
1050 break;
1051 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
1052 pos = startOfParagraph(startForPlatform());
1053 break;
1054 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
1055 pos = startForPlatform();
1056 if (isEditablePosition(pos.deepEquivalent()))
1057 pos = startOfEditableContent(pos);
1058 else
1059 pos = startOfDocument(pos);
1060 break;
1061 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1062 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1063 break;
1064 }
1065 adjustPositionForUserSelectAll(pos, !(directionOfEnclosingBlock() == TextDirection::LTR));
1066 return pos;
1067}

1069VisiblePosition FrameSelection::modifyMovingLeft(TextGranularity granularity, bool* reachedBoundary)
1070{
1071 if (reachedBoundary)

1074 switch (granularity) {

1096 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
1097 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
1098 // FIXME: Implement all of the above.
1099 pos = modifyMovingBackward(granularity, reachedBoundary);
1100 break;
1101 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:

1188static bool isBoundary(TextGranularity granularity)

1192
1193AXTextStateChangeIntent FrameSelection::textSelectionIntent(EAlteration alter, SelectionDirection direction, TextGranularity granularity)
1194{
1195 AXTextStateChangeIntent intent = AXTextStateChangeIntent();
1196 bool flip = false;
1197 if (alter == FrameSelection::AlterationMove) {
1198 intent.type = AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionMove;
1199 flip = isRange() && directionOfSelection() == TextDirection::RTL;
1200 } else
1201 intent.type = AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionExtend;
1202 switch (granularity) {
1203 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
1204 intent.selection.granularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityCharacter;
1205 break;
1206 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1207 intent.selection.granularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityWord;
1208 break;
1209 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1210 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
1211 intent.selection.granularity = AXTextSelectionGranularitySentence;
1212 break;
1213 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1214 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
1215 intent.selection.granularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityLine;
1216 break;
1217 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1218 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
1219 intent.selection.granularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityParagraph;
1220 break;
1221 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1222 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
1223 intent.selection.granularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityDocument;
1224 break;
1225 }
1226 bool boundary = false;
1227 switch (granularity) {
1228 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
1229 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1230 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1231 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1232 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1233 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1234 break;
1235 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary:
1236 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
1237 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary:
1238 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary:
1239 boundary = true;
1240 break;
1241 }
1242 switch (direction) {
1243 case SelectionDirection::Right:
1244 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
1245 if (boundary)
1246 intent.selection.direction = flip ? AXTextSelectionDirectionBeginning : AXTextSelectionDirectionEnd;
1247 else
1248 intent.selection.direction = flip ? AXTextSelectionDirectionPrevious : AXTextSelectionDirectionNext;
1249 break;
1250 case SelectionDirection::Left:
1251 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
1252 if (boundary)
1253 intent.selection.direction = flip ? AXTextSelectionDirectionEnd : AXTextSelectionDirectionBeginning;
1254 else
1255 intent.selection.direction = flip ? AXTextSelectionDirectionNext : AXTextSelectionDirectionPrevious;
1256 break;
1257 }
1258 return intent;
1259}
1260
1261static AXTextSelection textSelectionWithDirectionAndGranularity(SelectionDirection direction, TextGranularity granularity)
1262{
1263 // FIXME: Account for BIDI in SelectionDirection::Right & SelectionDirection::Left. (In a RTL block, Right would map to Previous/Beginning and Left to Next/End.)
1264 AXTextSelectionDirection intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionUnknown;
1265 switch (direction) {
1266 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
1267 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionNext;
1268 break;
1269 case SelectionDirection::Right:
1270 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionNext;
1271 break;
1272 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
1273 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionPrevious;
1274 break;
1275 case SelectionDirection::Left:
1276 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionPrevious;
1277 break;
1278 }
1279 AXTextSelectionGranularity intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityUnknown;
1280 switch (granularity) {
1281 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
1282 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityCharacter;
1283 break;
1284 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1285 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityWord;
1286 break;
1287 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1288 case TextGranularity::SentenceBoundary: // FIXME: Boundary should affect direction.
1289 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularitySentence;
1290 break;
1291 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1292 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityLine;
1293 break;
1294 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1295 case TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary: // FIXME: Boundary should affect direction.
1296 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityParagraph;
1297 break;
1298 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1299 case TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary: // FIXME: Boundary should affect direction.
1300 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityDocument;
1301 break;
1302 case TextGranularity::LineBoundary:
1303 intentGranularity = AXTextSelectionGranularityLine;
1304 switch (direction) {
1305 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
1306 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionEnd;
1307 break;
1308 case SelectionDirection::Right:
1309 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionEnd;
1310 break;
1311 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
1312 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionBeginning;
1313 break;
1314 case SelectionDirection::Left:
1315 intentDirection = AXTextSelectionDirectionBeginning;
1316 break;
1317 }
1318 break;
1319 }
1320 return { intentDirection, intentGranularity, false };
1321}
1322
1323bool FrameSelection::modify(EAlteration alter, SelectionDirection direction, TextGranularity granularity, EUserTriggered userTriggered)
1324{
1325 if (userTriggered == UserTriggered) {
1326 FrameSelection trialFrameSelection;
1327 trialFrameSelection.setSelection(m_selection);
1328 trialFrameSelection.modify(alter, direction, granularity, NotUserTriggered);
1329
1330 bool change = shouldChangeSelection(trialFrameSelection.selection());
1331 if (!change)
1332 return false;
1333
1334 if (trialFrameSelection.selection().isRange() && m_selection.isCaret() && !dispatchSelectStart())
1335 return false;
1336 }
1337
1338 willBeModified(alter, direction);
1339
1340 bool reachedBoundary = false;
1341 bool wasRange = m_selection.isRange();
1342 Position originalStartPosition = m_selection.start();
1343 VisiblePosition position;
1344 switch (direction) {
1345 case SelectionDirection::Right:
1346 if (alter == AlterationMove)
1347 position = modifyMovingRight(granularity, &reachedBoundary);
1348 else
1349 position = modifyExtendingRight(granularity);
1350 break;
1351 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
1352 if (alter == AlterationExtend)
1353 position = modifyExtendingForward(granularity);
1354 else
1355 position = modifyMovingForward(granularity, &reachedBoundary);
1356 break;
1357 case SelectionDirection::Left:
1358 if (alter == AlterationMove)
1359 position = modifyMovingLeft(granularity, &reachedBoundary);
1360 else
1361 position = modifyExtendingLeft(granularity);
1362 break;
1363 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
1364 if (alter == AlterationExtend)
1365 position = modifyExtendingBackward(granularity);
1366 else
1367 position = modifyMovingBackward(granularity, &reachedBoundary);
1368 break;
1369 }
1370
1371 if (reachedBoundary && !isRange() && userTriggered == UserTriggered && m_document && AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled()) {
1372 notifyAccessibilityForSelectionChange({ AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionBoundary, textSelectionWithDirectionAndGranularity(direction, granularity) });
1373 return true;
1374 }
1375
1376 if (position.isNull())
1377 return false;
1378
1379 if (m_document && isSpatialNavigationEnabled(m_document->frame())) {
1380 if (!wasRange && alter == AlterationMove && position == originalStartPosition)
1381 return false;
1382 }
1383
1384 if (m_document && AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled()) {
1385 if (AXObjectCache* cache = m_document->existingAXObjectCache())
1386 cache->setTextSelectionIntent(textSelectionIntent(alter, direction, granularity));
1387 }
1388
1389 // Some of the above operations set an xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation.
1390 // Setting a selection will clear it, so save it to possibly restore later.
1391 // Note: the Start position type is arbitrary because it is unused, it would be
1392 // the requested position type if there were no xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation set.
1393 LayoutUnit x = lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Start);
1394 m_selection.setIsDirectional(shouldAlwaysUseDirectionalSelection(m_document.get()) || alter == AlterationExtend);
1395
1396 switch (alter) {
1397 case AlterationMove:
1398 moveTo(position, userTriggered);
1399 break;
1400 case AlterationExtend:
1401
1402 if (!m_selection.isCaret()
1403 && (granularity == TextGranularity::WordGranularity || granularity == TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity || granularity == TextGranularity::LineGranularity)
1404 && m_document && !m_document->editor().behavior().shouldExtendSelectionByWordOrLineAcrossCaret()) {
1405 // Don't let the selection go across the base position directly. Needed to match mac
1406 // behavior when, for instance, word-selecting backwards starting with the caret in
1407 // the middle of a word and then word-selecting forward, leaving the caret in the
1408 // same place where it was, instead of directly selecting to the end of the word.
1409 VisibleSelection newSelection = m_selection;
1410 newSelection.setExtent(position);
1411 if (m_selection.isBaseFirst() != newSelection.isBaseFirst())
1412 position = m_selection.base();
1413 }
1414
1415 // Standard Mac behavior when extending to a boundary is grow the selection rather than leaving the
1416 // base in place and moving the extent. Matches NSTextView.
1417 if (!m_document || !m_document->editor().behavior().shouldAlwaysGrowSelectionWhenExtendingToBoundary() || m_selection.isCaret() || !isBoundary(granularity))
1418 setExtent(position, userTriggered);
1419 else {
1420 TextDirection textDirection = directionOfEnclosingBlock();
1421 if (direction == SelectionDirection::Forward || (textDirection == TextDirection::LTR && direction == SelectionDirection::Right) || (textDirection == TextDirection::RTL && direction == SelectionDirection::Left))
1422 setEnd(position, userTriggered);
1423 else
1424 setStart(position, userTriggered);
1425 }
1426 break;
1427 }
1428
1429 if (granularity == TextGranularity::LineGranularity || granularity == TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity)
1430 m_xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation = x;
1431
1432 if (userTriggered == UserTriggered)
1433 m_granularity = TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
1434
1435 setCaretRectNeedsUpdate();
1436
1437 return true;
1438}
1439
1440// FIXME: Maybe baseline would be better?
1441static bool absoluteCaretY(const VisiblePosition& c, int& y)
1442{
1443 IntRect rect = c.absoluteCaretBounds();
1444 if (rect.isEmpty())
1445 return false;
1446 y = rect.y() + rect.height() / 2;
1447 return true;
1448}
1449
1450bool FrameSelection::modify(EAlteration alter, unsigned verticalDistance, VerticalDirection direction, EUserTriggered userTriggered, CursorAlignOnScroll align)
1451{
1452 if (!verticalDistance)
1453 return false;
1454
1455 if (userTriggered == UserTriggered) {
1456 FrameSelection trialFrameSelection;
1457 trialFrameSelection.setSelection(m_selection);
1458 trialFrameSelection.modify(alter, verticalDistance, direction, NotUserTriggered);
1459
1460 bool change = shouldChangeSelection(trialFrameSelection.selection());
1461 if (!change)
1462 return false;
1463 }
1464
1465 willBeModified(alter, direction == DirectionUp ? SelectionDirection::Backward : SelectionDirection::Forward);
1466
1467 VisiblePosition pos;
1468 LayoutUnit xPos;
1469 switch (alter) {
1470 case AlterationMove:
1471 pos = VisiblePosition(direction == DirectionUp ? m_selection.start() : m_selection.end(), m_selection.affinity());
1472 xPos = lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(direction == DirectionUp ? Start : End);
1473 m_selection.setAffinity(direction == DirectionUp ? Affinity::Upstream : Affinity::Downstream);
1474 break;
1475 case AlterationExtend:
1476 pos = VisiblePosition(m_selection.extent(), m_selection.affinity());
1477 xPos = lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(Extent);
1478 m_selection.setAffinity(Affinity::Downstream);
1479 break;
1480 }
1481
1482 int startY;
1483 if (!absoluteCaretY(pos, startY))
1484 return false;
1485 if (direction == DirectionUp)
1486 startY = -startY;
1487 int lastY = startY;
1488
1489 VisiblePosition result;
1490 VisiblePosition next;
1491 for (VisiblePosition p = pos; ; p = next) {
1492 if (direction == DirectionUp)
1493 next = previousLinePosition(p, xPos);
1494 else
1495 next = nextLinePosition(p, xPos);
1496
1497 if (next.isNull() || next == p)
1498 break;
1499 int nextY;
1500 if (!absoluteCaretY(next, nextY))
1501 break;
1502 if (direction == DirectionUp)
1503 nextY = -nextY;
1504 if (nextY - startY > static_cast<int>(verticalDistance))
1505 break;
1506 if (nextY >= lastY) {
1507 lastY = nextY;
1508 result = next;
1509 }
1510 }
1511
1512 if (result.isNull())
1513 return false;
1514
1515 switch (alter) {
1516 case AlterationMove:
1517 moveTo(result, userTriggered, align);
1518 break;
1519 case AlterationExtend:
1520 setExtent(result, userTriggered);
1521 break;
1522 }
1523
1524 if (userTriggered == UserTriggered)
1525 m_granularity = TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
1526
1527 m_selection.setIsDirectional(shouldAlwaysUseDirectionalSelection(m_document.get()) || alter == AlterationExtend);
1528
1529 return true;
1530}
1531
1532LayoutUnit FrameSelection::lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation(PositionType type)
1533{
1534 if (isNone())
1535 return 0;
1536
1537 // FIXME: Can we use visibleStart/End/Extent?
1538 Position position;
1539 switch (type) {
1540 case Start:
1541 position = m_selection.start();
1542 break;
1543 case End:
1544 position = m_selection.end();
1545 break;
1546 case Extent:
1547 position = m_selection.extent();
1548 break;
1549 }
1550
1551 // FIXME: Why is this check needed? What's the harm in doing a little more work without a frame?
1552 if (!position.anchorNode()->document().frame())
1553 return 0;
1554
1555 // FIXME: Can we do this before getting the position from the selection?
1556 if (m_xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation)
1557 return *m_xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation;
1558
1559 // VisiblePosition creation can fail here if a node containing the selection becomes
1560 // visibility:hidden after the selection is created and before this function is called.
1561 VisiblePosition visiblePosition(position, m_selection.affinity());
1562 auto x = visiblePosition.isNotNull() ? visiblePosition.lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation() : 0;
1563 m_xPosForVerticalArrowNavigation = { x };
1564 return x;
1565}

1675
1676bool FrameSelection::recomputeCaretRect()
1677{
1678 if (!shouldUpdateCaretRect())
1679 return false;
1680
1681 if (!m_document)
1682 return false;
1683
1684 FrameView* v = m_document->view();
1685 if (!v)
1686 return false;
1687
1688 LayoutRect oldRect = localCaretRectWithoutUpdate();
1689
1690 RefPtr<Node> caretNode = m_previousCaretNode;
1691 if (shouldUpdateCaretRect()) {
1692 if (!isNonOrphanedCaret(m_selection))
1693 clearCaretRect();
1694 else {
1695 VisiblePosition visibleStart = m_selection.visibleStart();
1696 if (updateCaretRect(*m_document, visibleStart)) {
1697 caretNode = visibleStart.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode();
1698 m_absCaretBoundsDirty = true;
1699 }
1700 }
1701 }
1702 LayoutRect newRect = localCaretRectWithoutUpdate();
1703
1704 if (caretNode == m_previousCaretNode && oldRect == newRect && !m_absCaretBoundsDirty)
1705 return false;
1706
1707 IntRect oldAbsCaretBounds = m_absCaretBounds;
1708 bool isInsideFixed;
1709 m_absCaretBounds = absoluteBoundsForLocalCaretRect(rendererForCaretPainting(caretNode.get()), newRect, &isInsideFixed);
1710 m_caretInsidePositionFixed = isInsideFixed;
1711
1712 if (m_absCaretBoundsDirty && m_selection.isCaret()) // We should be able to always assert this condition.
1713 ASSERT(m_absCaretBounds == m_selection.visibleStart().absoluteCaretBounds());
1714
1715 m_absCaretBoundsDirty = false;
1716
1717 if (caretNode == m_previousCaretNode && oldAbsCaretBounds == m_absCaretBounds)
1718 return false;
1719
1720#if ENABLE(TEXT_CARET)
1721 if (RenderView* view = m_document->renderView()) {
1722 bool previousOrNewCaretNodeIsContentEditable = m_selection.isContentEditable() || (m_previousCaretNode && m_previousCaretNode->isContentEditable());
1723 if (shouldRepaintCaret(view, previousOrNewCaretNodeIsContentEditable)) {
1724 if (m_previousCaretNode)
1725 repaintCaretForLocalRect(m_previousCaretNode.get(), oldRect);
1726 m_previousCaretNode = caretNode;
1727 repaintCaretForLocalRect(caretNode.get(), newRect);
1728 }
1729 }
1730#endif
1731 return true;
1732}
1733
1734bool CaretBase::shouldRepaintCaret(const RenderView* view, bool isContentEditable) const
1735{
1736 ASSERT(view);
1737 Frame* frame = &view->frameView().frame(); // The frame where the selection started.
1738 bool caretBrowsing = frame && frame->settings().caretBrowsingEnabled();
1739 return (caretBrowsing || isContentEditable);
1740}

1747 CaretBase::invalidateCaretRect(m_selection.start().deprecatedNode(), recomputeCaretRect());
1748}
1749
1750void CaretBase::invalidateCaretRect(Node* node, bool caretRectChanged)
1751{
1752 // EDIT FIXME: This is an unfortunate hack.
1753 // Basically, we can't trust this layout position since we
1754 // can't guarantee that the check to see if we are in unrendered
1755 // content will work at this point. We may have to wait for
1756 // a layout and re-render of the document to happen. So, resetting this
1757 // flag will cause another caret layout to happen the first time
1758 // that we try to paint the caret after this call. That one will work since
1759 // it happens after the document has accounted for any editing
1760 // changes which may have been done.
1761 // And, we need to leave this layout here so the caret moves right
1762 // away after clicking.
1763 m_caretRectNeedsUpdate = true;
1764
1765 if (caretRectChanged)
1766 return;
1767
1768 if (RenderView* view = node->document().renderView()) {
1769 if (shouldRepaintCaret(view, isEditableNode(*node)))
1770 repaintCaretForLocalRect(node, localCaretRectWithoutUpdate());
1771 }
1772}

1780Color CaretBase::computeCaretColor(const RenderStyle& elementStyle, const Node* node)
1781{
1782 // On iOS, we want to fall back to the tintColor, and only override if CSS has explicitly specified a custom color.
1783#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY) && !PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
1784 UNUSED_PARAM(node);
1785 return elementStyle.caretColor();
1786#else
1787 auto* rootEditableElement = node ? node->rootEditableElement() : nullptr;
1788 auto* rootEditableStyle = rootEditableElement && rootEditableElement->renderer() ? &rootEditableElement->renderer()->style() : nullptr;
1789 // CSS value "auto" is treated as an invalid color.
1790 if (!elementStyle.caretColor().isValid() && rootEditableStyle) {
1791 auto rootEditableBackgroundColor = rootEditableStyle->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1792 auto elementBackgroundColor = elementStyle.visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1793 auto disappearsIntoBackground = blendSourceOver(rootEditableBackgroundColor, elementBackgroundColor) == rootEditableBackgroundColor;
1794 if (disappearsIntoBackground)
1795 return rootEditableStyle->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1796 }
1797 return elementStyle.visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyCaretColor);
1798#endif
1799}
1800
1801void CaretBase::paintCaret(const Node& node, GraphicsContext& context, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, const LayoutRect& clipRect) const
1802{
1803#if ENABLE(TEXT_CARET)
1804 if (m_caretVisibility == Hidden)
1805 return;
1806
1807 auto drawingRect = localCaretRectWithoutUpdate();
1808 if (auto* renderer = rendererForCaretPainting(&node))
1809 renderer->flipForWritingMode(drawingRect);
1810 drawingRect.moveBy(paintOffset);
1811 auto caret = intersection(drawingRect, clipRect);
1812 if (caret.isEmpty())
1813 return;
1814
1815 Color caretColor = Color::black;
1816 auto* element = is<Element>(node) ? downcast<Element>(&node) : node.parentElement();
1817 if (element && element->renderer())
1818 caretColor = CaretBase::computeCaretColor(element->renderer()->style(), &node);
1819
1820 auto pixelSnappedCaretRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(caret, node.document().deviceScaleFactor());
1821 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedCaretRect, caretColor);
1822#else
1823 UNUSED_PARAM(node);
1824 UNUSED_PARAM(context);
1825 UNUSED_PARAM(paintOffset);
1826 UNUSED_PARAM(clipRect);
1827#endif
1828}
1829
1830void FrameSelection::debugRenderer(RenderObject* renderer, bool selected) const
1831{
1832 if (is<Element>(*renderer->node())) {
1833 Element& element = downcast<Element>(*renderer->node());
1834 fprintf(stderr, "%s%s\n", selected ? "==> " : " ", element.localName().string().utf8().data());
1835 } else if (is<RenderText>(*renderer)) {
1836 RenderText& textRenderer = downcast<RenderText>(*renderer);
1837 if (textRenderer.text().isEmpty() || !textRenderer.firstTextBox()) {
1838 fprintf(stderr, "%s#text (empty)\n", selected ? "==> " : " ");
1839 return;
1840 }
1841
1842 static const int max = 36;
1843 String text = textRenderer.text();
1844 int textLength = text.length();
1845 if (selected) {
1846 int offset = 0;
1847 if (renderer->node() == m_selection.start().containerNode())
1848 offset = m_selection.start().computeOffsetInContainerNode();
1849 else if (renderer->node() == m_selection.end().containerNode())
1850 offset = m_selection.end().computeOffsetInContainerNode();
1851
1852 int pos;
1853 LegacyInlineTextBox* box = textRenderer.findNextInlineTextBox(offset, pos);
1854 text = text.substring(box->start(), box->len());
1855
1856 String show;
1857 int mid = max / 2;
1858 int caret = 0;
1859
1860 // text is shorter than max
1861 if (textLength < max) {
1862 show = text;
1863 caret = pos;
1864 } else if (pos - mid < 0) {
1865 // too few characters to left
1866 show = text.left(max - 3) + "...";
1867 caret = pos;
1868 } else if (pos - mid >= 0 && pos + mid <= textLength) {
1869 // enough characters on each side
1870 show = "..." + text.substring(pos - mid + 3, max - 6) + "...";
1871 caret = mid;
1872 } else {
1873 // too few characters on right
1874 show = "..." + text.right(max - 3);
1875 caret = pos - (textLength - show.length());
1876 }
1877
1878 show.replace('\n', ' ');
1879 show.replace('\r', ' ');
1880 fprintf(stderr, "==> #text : \"%s\" at offset %d\n", show.utf8().data(), pos);
1881 fprintf(stderr, " ");
1882 for (int i = 0; i < caret; i++)
1883 fprintf(stderr, " ");
1884 fprintf(stderr, "^\n");
1885 } else {
1886 if ((int)text.length() > max)
1887 text = text.left(max - 3) + "...";
1888 else
1889 text = text.left(max);
1890 fprintf(stderr, " #text : \"%s\"\n", text.utf8().data());
1891 }
1892 }
1893}
1894
1895bool FrameSelection::contains(const LayoutPoint& point) const
1896{
1897 // Treat a collapsed selection like no selection.
1898 if (!isRange())
1899 return false;
1900
1901 auto range = m_selection.firstRange();
1902 if (!range)
1903 return false;
1904
1905 if (!m_document)
1906 return false;
1907
1908 HitTestResult result(point);
1909 m_document->hitTest(HitTestRequest(), result);
1910 Node* innerNode = result.innerNode();
1911 if (!innerNode || !innerNode->renderer())
1912 return false;
1913
1914 return WebCore::contains<ComposedTree>(*range, makeBoundaryPoint(innerNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(result.localPoint(), nullptr)));
1915}
1916
1917// Workaround for the fact that it's hard to delete a frame.
1918// Call this after doing user-triggered selections to make it easy to delete the frame you entirely selected.
1919// Can't do this implicitly as part of every setSelection call because in some contexts it might not be good
1920// for the focus to move to another frame. So instead we call it from places where we are selecting with the
1921// mouse or the keyboard after setting the selection.
1922void FrameSelection::selectFrameElementInParentIfFullySelected()
1923{
1924 // Find the parent frame; if there is none, then we have nothing to do.
1925 auto document = makeRefPtr(m_document.get());
1926 if (!document)
1927 return;
1928 auto frame = makeRefPtr(document->frame());
1929 if (!frame)
1930 return;
1931 auto parent = makeRefPtr(frame->tree().parent());
1932 if (!parent)
1933 return;
1934 Page* page = m_document->page();
1935 if (!page)
1936 return;
1937
1938 // Check if the selection contains the entire frame contents; if not, then there is nothing to do.
1939 if (!isRange())
1940 return;
1941 if (!isStartOfDocument(selection().visibleStart()))
1942 return;
1943 if (!isEndOfDocument(selection().visibleEnd()))
1944 return;
1945
1946 // Get to the <iframe> or <frame> (or even <object>) element in the parent frame.
1947 auto ownerElement = makeRefPtr(m_document->ownerElement());
1948 if (!ownerElement)
1949 return;
1950 auto ownerElementParent = makeRefPtr(ownerElement->parentNode());
1951 if (!ownerElementParent)
1952 return;
1953
1954 // This method's purpose is it to make it easier to select iframes (in order to delete them). Don't do anything if the iframe isn't deletable.
1955 if (!ownerElementParent->hasEditableStyle())
1956 return;
1957
1958 // Create compute positions before and after the element.
1959 unsigned ownerElementNodeIndex = ownerElement->computeNodeIndex();
1960 VisiblePosition beforeOwnerElement(VisiblePosition(Position(ownerElementParent.get(), ownerElementNodeIndex, Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor)));
1961 VisiblePosition afterOwnerElement(VisiblePosition(Position(ownerElementParent.get(), ownerElementNodeIndex + 1, Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor), Affinity::Upstream));
1962
1963 // Focus on the parent frame, and then select from before this element to after.
1964 VisibleSelection newSelection(beforeOwnerElement, afterOwnerElement);
1965 if (parent->selection().shouldChangeSelection(newSelection)) {
1966 page->focusController().setFocusedFrame(parent.get());
1967 // Previous focus can trigger DOM events, ensure the selection did not become orphan.
1968 if (newSelection.isOrphan())
1969 parent->selection().clear();
1970 else
1971 parent->selection().setSelection(newSelection);
1972 }
1973}
1974
1975void FrameSelection::selectAll()
1976{
1977 Element* focusedElement = m_document->focusedElement();
1978 if (is<HTMLSelectElement>(focusedElement)) {
1979 HTMLSelectElement& selectElement = downcast<HTMLSelectElement>(*focusedElement);
1980 if (selectElement.canSelectAll()) {
1981 selectElement.selectAll();
1982 return;
1983 }
1984 }
1985
1986 RefPtr<Node> root;
1987 Node* selectStartTarget = nullptr;
1988 if (m_selection.isContentEditable()) {
1989 root = highestEditableRoot(m_selection.start());
1990 if (Node* shadowRoot = m_selection.nonBoundaryShadowTreeRootNode())
1991 selectStartTarget = shadowRoot->shadowHost();
1992 else
1993 selectStartTarget = root.get();
1994 } else {
1995 if (m_selection.isNone() && focusedElement) {
1996 if (focusedElement->isTextField()) {
1997 downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*focusedElement).select();
1998 return;
1999 }
2000 root = focusedElement->nonBoundaryShadowTreeRootNode();
2001 } else
2002 root = m_selection.nonBoundaryShadowTreeRootNode();
2003
2004 if (root)
2005 selectStartTarget = root->shadowHost();
2006 else {
2007 root = m_document->documentElement();
2008 selectStartTarget = m_document->bodyOrFrameset();
2009 }
2010 }
2011 if (!root)
2012 return;
2013
2014 if (selectStartTarget) {
2015 auto event = Event::create(eventNames().selectstartEvent, Event::CanBubble::Yes, Event::IsCancelable::Yes);
2016 selectStartTarget->dispatchEvent(event);
2017 if (event->defaultPrevented())
2018 return;
2019 }
2020
2021 VisibleSelection newSelection(VisibleSelection::selectionFromContentsOfNode(root.get()));
2022
2023 if (shouldChangeSelection(newSelection)) {
2024 AXTextStateChangeIntent intent(AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionExtend, AXTextSelection { AXTextSelectionDirectionDiscontiguous, AXTextSelectionGranularityAll, false });
2025 setSelection(newSelection, defaultSetSelectionOptions() | FireSelectEvent, intent);
2026 }
2027}

2029bool FrameSelection::setSelectedRange(const std::optional<SimpleRange>& range, Affinity affinity, ShouldCloseTyping closeTyping, EUserTriggered userTriggered)
2030{
2031 if (!range)
2032 return false;
2033
2034 if (&range->start.document() != &range->end.document())
2035 return false;
2036
2037 VisibleSelection newSelection(*range, affinity);
2038
2039#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2040 // FIXME: Why do we need this check only in iOS?
2041 if (newSelection.isNone())
2042 return false;
2043#endif
2044
2045 OptionSet<SetSelectionOption> selectionOptions { ClearTypingStyle };
2046 if (closeTyping == ShouldCloseTyping::Yes)
2047 selectionOptions.add(CloseTyping);
2048
2049 if (userTriggered == UserTriggered) {
2050 FrameSelection trialFrameSelection;
2051
2052 trialFrameSelection.setSelection(newSelection, selectionOptions);
2053
2054 if (!shouldChangeSelection(trialFrameSelection.selection()))
2055 return false;
2056
2057 selectionOptions.add(IsUserTriggered);
2058 }
2059
2060 setSelection(newSelection, selectionOptions);
2061 return true;
2062}

2124
2125void FrameSelection::updateAppearance()
2126{
2127#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2128 if (!m_updateAppearanceEnabled)
2129 return;
2130#endif
2131
2132 // Paint a block cursor instead of a caret in overtype mode unless the caret is at the end of a line (in this case
2133 // the FrameSelection will paint a blinking caret as usual).
2134 VisibleSelection oldSelection = selection();
2135
2136#if ENABLE(TEXT_CARET)
2137 bool paintBlockCursor = m_shouldShowBlockCursor && m_selection.isCaret() && !isLogicalEndOfLine(m_selection.visibleEnd());
2138 bool caretRectChangedOrCleared = recomputeCaretRect();
2139
2140 bool caretBrowsing = m_document->settings().caretBrowsingEnabled();
2141 bool shouldBlink = !paintBlockCursor && caretIsVisible() && isCaret() && (oldSelection.isContentEditable() || caretBrowsing);
2142
2143 // If the caret moved, stop the blink timer so we can restart with a
2144 // black caret in the new location.
2145 if (caretRectChangedOrCleared || !shouldBlink || shouldStopBlinkingDueToTypingCommand(m_document.get()))
2146 m_caretBlinkTimer.stop();
2147
2148 // Start blinking with a black caret. Be sure not to restart if we're
2149 // already blinking in the right location.
2150 if (shouldBlink && !m_caretBlinkTimer.isActive()) {
2151 if (Seconds blinkInterval = RenderTheme::singleton().caretBlinkInterval())
2152 m_caretBlinkTimer.startRepeating(blinkInterval);
2153
2154 if (!m_caretPaint) {
2155 m_caretPaint = true;
2156 invalidateCaretRect();
2157 }
2158 }
2159#endif
2160
2161 RenderView* view = m_document->renderView();
2162 if (!view)
2163 return;
2164
2165 // Construct a new VisibleSolution, since m_selection is not necessarily valid, and the following steps
2166 // assume a valid selection. See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=69563> and <rdar://problem/10232866>.
2167#if ENABLE(TEXT_CARET)
2168 VisiblePosition endVisiblePosition = paintBlockCursor ? modifyExtendingForward(TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity) : oldSelection.visibleEnd();
2169 VisibleSelection selection(oldSelection.visibleStart(), endVisiblePosition);
2170#else
2171 VisibleSelection selection(oldSelection.visibleStart(), oldSelection.visibleEnd());
2172#endif
2173
2174 if (!selection.isRange()) {
2175 view->selection().clear();
2176 return;
2177 }
2178
2179 // Use the rightmost candidate for the start of the selection, and the leftmost candidate for the end of the selection.
2180 // Example: foo <a>bar</a>. Imagine that a line wrap occurs after 'foo', and that 'bar' is selected. If we pass [foo, 3]
2181 // as the start of the selection, the selection painting code will think that content on the line containing 'foo' is selected
2182 // and will fill the gap before 'bar'.
2183 Position startPos = selection.start();
2184 Position candidate = startPos.downstream();
2185 if (candidate.isCandidate())
2186 startPos = candidate;
2187 Position endPos = selection.end();
2188 candidate = endPos.upstream();
2189 if (candidate.isCandidate())
2190 endPos = candidate;
2191
2192 // We can get into a state where the selection endpoints map to the same VisiblePosition when a selection is deleted
2193 // because we don't yet notify the FrameSelection of text removal.
2194 if (startPos.isNotNull() && endPos.isNotNull() && selection.visibleStart() != selection.visibleEnd()) {
2195 RenderObject* startRenderer = startPos.deprecatedNode()->renderer();
2196 int startOffset = startPos.deprecatedEditingOffset();
2197 RenderObject* endRenderer = endPos.deprecatedNode()->renderer();
2198 int endOffset = endPos.deprecatedEditingOffset();
2199 ASSERT(startOffset >= 0 && endOffset >= 0);
2200 view->selection().set({ startRenderer, endRenderer, static_cast<unsigned>(startOffset), static_cast<unsigned>(endOffset) });
2201 }
2202}

2239// Helper function that tells whether a particular node is an element that has an entire
2240// Frame and FrameView, a <frame>, <iframe>, or <object>.
2241static bool isFrameElement(const Node* n)
2242{
2243 if (!n)
2244 return false;
2245 RenderObject* renderer = n->renderer();
2246 if (!is<RenderWidget>(renderer))
2247 return false;
2248 Widget* widget = downcast<RenderWidget>(*renderer).widget();
2249 return widget && widget->isFrameView();
2250}
2251
2252void FrameSelection::setFocusedElementIfNeeded()
2253{
2254 if (isNone() || !isFocused())
2255 return;
2256
2257 bool caretBrowsing = m_document->settings().caretBrowsingEnabled();
2258 if (caretBrowsing) {
2259 if (Element* anchor = enclosingAnchorElement(m_selection.base())) {
2260 m_document->page()->focusController().setFocusedElement(anchor, *m_document->frame());
2261 return;
2262 }
2263 }
2264
2265 if (Element* target = m_selection.rootEditableElement()) {
2266 // Walk up the DOM tree to search for an element to focus.
2267 while (target) {
2268 // We don't want to set focus on a subframe when selecting in a parent frame,
2269 // so add the !isFrameElement check here. There's probably a better way to make this
2270 // work in the long term, but this is the safest fix at this time.
2271 if (target->isMouseFocusable() && !isFrameElement(target)) {
2272 m_document->page()->focusController().setFocusedElement(target, *m_document->frame());
2273 return;
2274 }
2275 target = target->parentOrShadowHostElement();
2276 }
2277 m_document->setFocusedElement(nullptr);
2278 }
2279
2280 if (caretBrowsing)
2281 m_document->page()->focusController().setFocusedElement(nullptr, *m_document->frame());
2282}

2333void FrameSelection::getClippedVisibleTextRectangles(Vector<FloatRect>& rectangles, TextRectangleHeight textRectHeight) const
2334{
2335 if (!m_document->renderView())
2336 return;
2337
2338 auto range = selection().toNormalizedRange();
2339 if (!range)
2340 return;

2343 if (textRectHeight == TextRectangleHeight::SelectionHeight)
2344 behavior.add(RenderObject::BoundingRectBehavior::UseSelectionHeight);

2347 for (auto& rect : boundingBoxes(RenderObject::absoluteTextQuads(*range, behavior))) {

2350 rectangles.append(intersectionRect);

2354// Scans logically forward from "start", including any child frames.
2355static HTMLFormElement* scanForForm(Element* start)
2356{
2357 if (!start)
2358 return nullptr;
2359 for (auto& element : descendantsOfType<HTMLElement>(start->document())) {
2360 if (is<HTMLFormElement>(element))
2361 return &downcast<HTMLFormElement>(element);
2362 if (is<HTMLFormControlElement>(element))
2363 return downcast<HTMLFormControlElement>(element).form();
2364 if (is<HTMLFrameElementBase>(element)) {
2365 if (auto* contentDocument = downcast<HTMLFrameElementBase>(element).contentDocument()) {
2366 if (auto* frameResult = scanForForm(contentDocument->documentElement()))
2367 return frameResult;
2368 }
2369 }
2370 }
2371 return nullptr;
2372}

2374// We look for either the form containing the current focus, or for one immediately after it
2375HTMLFormElement* FrameSelection::currentForm() const
2376{
2377 // Start looking either at the active (first responder) node, or where the selection is.
2378 Element* start = m_document->focusedElement();
2379 if (!start)
2380 start = m_selection.start().element();
2381 if (!start)
2382 return nullptr;
2383
2384 if (auto form = lineageOfType<HTMLFormElement>(*start).first())
2385 return form;
2386 if (auto formControl = lineageOfType<HTMLFormControlElement>(*start).first())
2387 return formControl->form();
2388
2389 // Try walking forward in the node tree to find a form element.
2390 return scanForForm(start);
2391}

2393void FrameSelection::revealSelection(SelectionRevealMode revealMode, const ScrollAlignment& alignment, RevealExtentOption revealExtentOption, ScrollBehavior scrollBehavior, SmoothScrollFeatureEnablement overrideFeatureEnablement)
2394{
2395 if (revealMode == SelectionRevealMode::DoNotReveal)
2396 return;
2397
2398 if (isNone())
2399 return;
2400
2401 LayoutRect rect;
2402 bool insideFixed = false;
2403 if (isCaret())
2404 rect = absoluteCaretBounds(&insideFixed);
2405 else
2406 rect = revealExtentOption == RevealExtent ? VisiblePosition(m_selection.extent()).absoluteCaretBounds() : enclosingIntRect(selectionBounds(ClipToVisibleContent::No));
2407
2408 Position start = m_selection.start();
2409 ASSERT(start.deprecatedNode());
2410 if (start.deprecatedNode() && start.deprecatedNode()->renderer()) {
2411#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2412 if (RenderLayer* layer = start.deprecatedNode()->renderer()->enclosingLayer()) {
2413 if (!m_scrollingSuppressCount) {
2414 auto* scrollableArea = layer->ensureLayerScrollableArea();
2415 scrollableArea->setAdjustForIOSCaretWhenScrolling(true);
2416 layer->scrollRectToVisible(rect, insideFixed, { revealMode, alignment, alignment, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::Yes, scrollBehavior, overrideFeatureEnablement});
2417 scrollableArea->setAdjustForIOSCaretWhenScrolling(false);
2418 updateAppearance();
2419 if (m_document->page())
2420 m_document->page()->chrome().client().notifyRevealedSelectionByScrollingFrame(*m_document->frame());
2421 }
2422 }
2423#else
2424 // FIXME: This code only handles scrolling the startContainer's layer, but
2425 // the selection rect could intersect more than just that.
2426 // See <rdar://problem/4799899>.
2427 if (start.deprecatedNode()->renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(rect, insideFixed, { revealMode, alignment, alignment, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::Yes, scrollBehavior, overrideFeatureEnablement}))
2428 updateAppearance();
2429#endif
2430 }
2431}

2573UChar FrameSelection::characterInRelationToCaretSelection(int amount) const
2574{
2575 auto position = m_selection.visibleStart();
2576 if (amount < 0) {
2577 int count = abs(amount);
2578 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
2579 position = position.previous();
2580 return position.characterBefore();
2581 }
2582 for (int i = 0; i < amount; i++)
2583 position = position.next();
2584 return position.characterAfter();
2585}

2587bool FrameSelection::selectionAtWordStart() const
2588{
2589 auto position = m_selection.visibleStart();
2590 if (isStartOfParagraph(position))
2591 return true;
2592
2593 unsigned previousCount = 0;
2594 for (position = position.previous(); !position.isNull(); position = position.previous()) {
2595 previousCount++;
2596 if (isStartOfParagraph(position))
2597 return previousCount != 1;
2598 if (UChar c = position.characterAfter())
2599 return isSpaceOrNewline(c) || c == noBreakSpace || (u_ispunct(c) && c != ',' && c != '-' && c != '\'');
2600 }
2601 return true;
2602}
