2614VisibleSelection FrameSelection::wordSelectionContainingCaretSelection(const VisibleSelection& selection)
2615{
2616 if (selection.isNone())
2617 return VisibleSelection();
2618
2619 ASSERT(selection.isCaretOrRange());
2620 FrameSelection frameSelection;
2621 frameSelection.setSelection(selection);
2622
2623 Position startPosBeforeExpansion(selection.start());
2624 Position endPosBeforeExpansion(selection.end());
2625 VisiblePosition startVisiblePosBeforeExpansion(startPosBeforeExpansion);
2626 VisiblePosition endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion(endPosBeforeExpansion);
2627 if (endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion.isNull())
2628 return VisibleSelection();
2629
2630 if (isEndOfParagraph(endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion)) {
2631 UChar c(endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion.characterBefore());
2632 if (isSpaceOrNewline(c) || c == noBreakSpace) {
2633 // End of paragraph with space.
2634 return VisibleSelection();
2635 }
2636 }
2637
2638 // If at end of paragraph, move backwards one character.
2639 // This has the effect of selecting the word on the line (which is
2640 // what we want, rather than selecting past the end of the line).
2641 if (isEndOfParagraph(endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion) && !isStartOfParagraph(endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion))
2642 frameSelection.modify(FrameSelection::AlterationMove, SelectionDirection::Backward, TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity);
2643
2644 VisibleSelection newSelection = frameSelection.selection();
2645 newSelection.expandUsingGranularity(TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
2646 frameSelection.setSelection(newSelection, defaultSetSelectionOptions(), AXTextStateChangeIntent(), AlignCursorOnScrollIfNeeded, frameSelection.granularity());
2647
2648 Position startPos(frameSelection.selection().start());
2649 Position endPos(frameSelection.selection().end());
2650
2651 // Expansion cannot be allowed to change selection so that it is no longer
2652 // touches (or contains) the original, unexpanded selection.
2653 // Enforce this on the way into these additional calculations to give them
2654 // the best chance to yield a suitable answer.
2655 if (startPos > startPosBeforeExpansion)
2656 startPos = startPosBeforeExpansion;
2657 if (endPos < endPosBeforeExpansion)
2658 endPos = endPosBeforeExpansion;
2659
2660 VisiblePosition startVisiblePos(startPos);
2661 VisiblePosition endVisiblePos(endPos);
2662
2663 if (startVisiblePos.isNull() || endVisiblePos.isNull()) {
2664 // Start or end is nil
2665 return VisibleSelection();
2666 }
2667
2668 if (isEndOfLine(endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion)) {
2669 VisiblePosition previous(endVisiblePos.previous());
2670 if (previous == endVisiblePos) {
2671 // Empty document
2672 return VisibleSelection();
2673 }
2674 UChar c(previous.characterAfter());
2675 if (isSpaceOrNewline(c) || c == noBreakSpace) {
2676 // Space at end of line
2677 return VisibleSelection();
2678 }
2679 }
2680
2681 // Expansion has selected past end of line.
2682 // Try repositioning backwards.
2683 if (isEndOfLine(startVisiblePos) && isStartOfLine(endVisiblePos)) {
2684 VisiblePosition previous(startVisiblePos.previous());
2685 if (isEndOfLine(previous)) {
2686 // On empty line
2687 return VisibleSelection();
2688 }
2689 UChar c(previous.characterAfter());
2690 if (isSpaceOrNewline(c) || c == noBreakSpace) {
2691 // Space at end of line
2692 return VisibleSelection();
2693 }
2694 frameSelection.moveTo(startVisiblePos);
2695 frameSelection.modify(FrameSelection::AlterationExtend, SelectionDirection::Backward, TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
2696 startPos = frameSelection.selection().start();
2697 endPos = frameSelection.selection().end();
2698 startVisiblePos = VisiblePosition(startPos);
2699 endVisiblePos = VisiblePosition(endPos);
2700 if (startVisiblePos.isNull() || endVisiblePos.isNull()) {
2701 // Start or end is nil
2702 return VisibleSelection();
2703 }
2704 }
2705
2706 // Now loop backwards until we find a non-space.
2707 while (endVisiblePos != startVisiblePos) {
2708 VisiblePosition previous(endVisiblePos.previous());
2709 UChar c(previous.characterAfter());
2710 if (!isSpaceOrNewline(c) && c != noBreakSpace)
2711 break;
2712 endVisiblePos = previous;
2713 }
2714
2715 // Expansion cannot be allowed to change selection so that it is no longer
2716 // touches (or contains) the original, unexpanded selection.
2717 // Enforce this on the way out of the function to preserve the invariant.
2718 if (startVisiblePos > startVisiblePosBeforeExpansion)
2719 startVisiblePos = startVisiblePosBeforeExpansion;
2720 if (endVisiblePos < endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion)
2721 endVisiblePos = endVisiblePosBeforeExpansion;
2722
2723 return VisibleSelection(startVisiblePos, endVisiblePos);
2724}

2726bool FrameSelection::selectionAtSentenceStart() const
2727{
2728 auto position = m_selection.visibleStart();
2729 if (position.isNull())
2730 return false;
2731
2732 if (isStartOfParagraph(position))
2733 return true;
2734
2735 bool sawSpace = false;
2736 unsigned previousCount = 0;
2737 for (position = position.previous(); !position.isNull(); position = position.previous()) {
2738 previousCount++;
2739 if (isStartOfParagraph(position))
2740 return previousCount != 1 && (previousCount != 2 || !sawSpace);
2741 if (auto c = position.characterAfter()) {
2742 if (isSpaceOrNewline(c) || c == noBreakSpace)
2743 sawSpace = true;
2744 else
2745 return c == '.' || c == '!' || c == '?';
2746 }
2747 }
2748 return true;
2749}

2751std::optional<SimpleRange> FrameSelection::rangeByAlteringCurrentSelection(EAlteration alteration, int amount) const
2752{
2753 if (m_selection.isNone())
2754 return std::nullopt;
2755
2756 if (!amount)
2757 return m_selection.toNormalizedRange();
2758
2759 FrameSelection frameSelection;
2760 frameSelection.setSelection(m_selection);
2761 SelectionDirection direction = amount > 0 ? SelectionDirection::Forward : SelectionDirection::Backward;
2762 for (int i = 0; i < abs(amount); i++)
2763 frameSelection.modify(alteration, direction, TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity);
2764 return frameSelection.selection().toNormalizedRange();
2765}

2800static bool containsEndpoints(const WeakPtr<Document>& document, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& range)
2801{
2802 return document && range && document->contains(range->start.container) && document->contains(range->end.container);
2803}
2804
2805static bool containsEndpoints(const WeakPtr<Document>& document, const Range& liveRange)
2806{
2807 // Only need to check the start container because live ranges enforce the invariant that start and end have a common ancestor.
2808 return document && document->contains(liveRange.startContainer());
2809}

2838void FrameSelection::associateLiveRange(Range& liveRange)
2839{

2842 liveRange.didAssociateWithSelection();

2846void FrameSelection::updateFromAssociatedLiveRange()
2847{
2848 ASSERT(m_associatedLiveRange);
2849 if (!containsEndpoints(m_document, *m_associatedLiveRange))
2850 disassociateLiveRange();
2851 else {
2852 // Don't use VisibleSelection's constructor that takes a SimpleRange, because it uses makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition instead of makeContainerOffsetPosition.
2853 auto start = makeContainerOffsetPosition(&m_associatedLiveRange->startContainer(), m_associatedLiveRange->startOffset());
2854 auto end = makeContainerOffsetPosition(&m_associatedLiveRange->endContainer(), m_associatedLiveRange->endOffset());
2855 setSelection({ start, end });
2856 }
2857}
2858
2859void FrameSelection::updateAssociatedLiveRange()
2860{
2861 auto range = m_selection.range();
2862 if (!containsEndpoints(m_document, range)) {
2863 // The selection was cleared or is now within a shadow tree.
2864 disassociateLiveRange();
2865 } else {
2866 if (m_associatedLiveRange)
2867 m_associatedLiveRange->updateFromSelection(*range);
2868 }
2869}
